Nairobi Governor candidate Johnson Sakaja will be launching his manifesto for the county on
Thursday, July 21, 2022, ahead of the August general elections. DP Ruto, the Kenya Kwanza flagbearer took to social media on Wednesday to hail Sakaja’s manifesto saying it will focus on
transforming the capital's economy. “UDA Nairobi County
governor candidate @SakajaJohnson
will launch his manifesto aimed at transforming the city on Thursday 21st, July
at 8 pm. Let’s make Nairobi work,” Ruto wrote on Twitter.  Sakaja will be contesting against nine other candidates including, Polycarp Igathe, Agnes Kagure, Denise Kodhe, Esther Waringa Thairu, Harman
Singh Grewal, Kenneth Nyamwamu, Nancy Wambui Mwadime and Cleophas Kiio Mutua